All Progressives Congress (APC) governors have resolved their differences, ahead of the national convention. The event will be held on Saturday, March 26 at Eagle Square in Abuja. Nasarawa State Governor, Abdullahi Sule, announced that all his colleagues were now on good terms. Sule, the Chairman of Media Committee, spoke on Monday through Garba Shehu, the Secretary. The APC under Yobe Governor Mai Buni and the Caretaker and Extraordinary Convention Planning Committee (CECPC) are making efforts to take everyone along, Sule said. “I believe it is the only path for a successful convention and victory at elections. “We believe in unity in diversity, and this is the mantra of our convention.” Sule assured that necessary arrangements were on to ensure a successful outing. About 4,000 delegates from the 36 states and the FCT are expected at the convention to elect new national executives.